SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 388.055 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 388.055 Each public school, including, without limitation, each
3 charter school, shall : [, to the extent that money is available for that
4 purpose:]
5 1. Employ a school counselor at the school on a full-time basis.
6 2. Provide for a comprehensive program for school counseling
7 developed by a school counselor pursuant to NRS 391.293.
8 Sec. 2. NRS 388.1344 is hereby amended to read as follows:
9 388.1344 1. Each school safety team established pursuant to
10 NRS 388.1343 must consist of the administrator of the school or his
11 or her designee and the following persons appointed by the
12 administrator:
13 (a) A school counselor, school psychologist or social worker ;
14 [if the school employs a person in such a position full-time;]
15 (b) At least one teacher who teaches at the school;
16 (c) At least one parent or legal guardian of a pupil enrolled in
17 the school;
18 (d) A school police officer or school resource officer if the
19 school employs a person in such a position full-time;
20 (e) For a middle school, junior high school or high school, one
21 pupil enrolled in the school; and
22 (f) Any other persons appointed by the administrator.
23 2. The administrator of the school or his or her designee shall
24 serve as the chair of the school safety team.
25 3. The school safety team shall:
26 (a) Meet at least two times each year;
27 (b) Identify and address patterns of discrimination based on
28 race, bullying or cyber-bullying;
29 (c) Review and strengthen school policies to prevent and
30 address discrimination based on race, bullying or cyber-bullying;
31 (d) Provide information to school personnel, pupils enrolled in
32 the school and parents and legal guardians of pupils enrolled in the
33 school on methods to address bullying and cyber-bullying;
34 (e) To the extent practicable, work with members of the
35 community with expertise in cultural competency; and
36 (f) To the extent money is available, participate in any training
37 conducted by the school district or school regarding bullying and
38 cyber-bullying.
39 4. To the extent practicable, the school safety team must
40 consist of members who are representative of the demographic
41 groups identified in subsection 1 of NRS 388.1235.
