1 Sec. 3. NRS 388.14553 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 388.14553 1. The board of trustees of a school district or the
3 governing body of a charter school shall:
4 (a) Appoint a team of at least three members of the staff of each
5 public school, other than a charter school, that is located in the
6 school district or of the charter school, as applicable, including,
7 without limitation, a school counselor, psychologist, social worker
8 or a similar person [, if the school employs such a person on a full-
9 time basis,] and a school administrator. The team must receive
10 notification if the support center receives:
11 (1) A report through the SafeVoice Program of any
12 dangerous, violent or unlawful activity which is being conducted, or
13 is threatened to be conducted, on the property of the school, at an
14 activity sponsored by the school, on a school bus of the school or by
15 a pupil enrolled at the school; or
16 (2) Notification through the Handle with Care Program of a
17 pupil who was exposed to a traumatic event.
18 (b) Ensure that information concerning the SafeVoice Program,
19 including, without limitation, the telephone number for the hotline
20 established pursuant to NRS 388.1455:
21 (1) Appears on the back of any identification card issued to
22 pupils and staff at the school; and
23 (2) Is posted in conspicuous locations around the school,
24 which may include, without limitation, the front office, the cafeteria
25 or a school bus.
26 2. Upon receiving notification from the support center through
27 the SafeVoice Program or the Handle with Care Program, a member
28 of the appropriate team appointed pursuant to paragraph (a) of
29 subsection 1 shall take appropriate action in accordance with the
30 training he or she has received pursuant to NRS 388.1455 or
31 388.14538 to respond to the activity, threat or traumatic event, as
32 applicable.
33 3. The team appointed pursuant to paragraph (a) of subsection
34 1 may:
35 (a) Include a person appointed by the public school pursuant to
36 NRS 388.247 to a committee to review the plan developed for the
37 school pursuant to NRS 388.243.
38 (b) Allow another person to temporarily serve on the team if a
39 member of the team is unavailable.
40 Sec. 4. The provisions of NRS 354.599 do not apply to any
41 additional expenses of a local government that are related to the
42 provisions of this act.
43 Sec. 5. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
